The paper deals with the task of natural language object retrieval, which involves processing natural language queries and images to localize objects within the scene. This task involves both computer vision and natural language processing, making it likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed model involves integrating spatial configurations and global scene-level contextual information, which suggests it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the model utilizes a recurrent network and can transfer visual-linguistic knowledge, indicating it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
